<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:51;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:52;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:209:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_HTTPPROXYTUNNEL</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to tunnel through a given HTTP proxy.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:53;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:54;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:288:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_MUTE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to be completely silent with regards to
the cURL functions.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Removed in cURL 7.15.5 (You can use CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER instead)
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:55;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:56;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:312:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_NETRC</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to scan the <var class="filename">~/.netrc</var>
file to find a username and password for the remote site that
a connection is being established with.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:57;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:58;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:292:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_NOBODY</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to exclude the body from the output.
Request method is then set to HEAD. Changing this to <b>FALSE</b> does
not change it to GET.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:59;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:60;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:417:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_NOPROGRESS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><p>
<b>TRUE</b> to disable the progress meter for cURL transfers.
</p><blockquote class="note"><p><strong class="note">Note</strong>:
</p><p>
PHP automatically sets this option to <b>TRUE</b>, this should only be
changed for debugging purposes.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:61;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:62;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:355:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_NOSIGNAL</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to ignore any cURL function that causes a
signal to be sent to the PHP process. This is turned on by default
in multi-threaded SAPIs so timeout options can still be used.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:63;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:64;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:294:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_POST</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to do a regular HTTP POST. This POST is the
normal <em>application/x-www-form-urlencoded</em> kind,
most commonly used by HTML forms.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:65;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:66;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:265:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PUT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to HTTP PUT a file. The file to PUT must
be set with <b>CURLOPT_INFILE</b> and
<b>CURLOPT_INFILESIZE</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:67;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:68;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:316:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_RETURNTRANSFER</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to return the transfer as a string of the
return value of <span class="function">{@see curl_exec()}</span> instead of outputting
it out directly.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:69;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:70;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:503:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SAFE_UPLOAD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to disable support for the <em>@</em> prefix for
uploading files in <b>CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS</b>, which
means that values starting with <em>@</em> can be safely
passed as fields. {@see CURLFile} may be used for
uploads instead.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in PHP 5.5.0 with <b>FALSE</b> as the default value. PHP 5.6.0
changes the default value to <b>TRUE</b>.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:71;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:72;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:484:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>FALSE</b> to stop cURL from verifying the peer\'s
certificate. Alternate certificates to verify against can be
specified with the <b>CURLOPT_CAINFO</b> option
or a certificate directory can be specified with the
<b>CURLOPT_CAPATH</b> option.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> by default as of cURL 7.10. Default bundle installed as of
cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:73;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:74;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:332:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_TRANSFERTEXT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to use ASCII mode for FTP transfers.
For LDAP, it retrieves data in plain text instead of HTML. On
Windows systems, it will not set <em>STDOUT</em> to binary
mode.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:75;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:76;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:315:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_UNRESTRICTED_AUTH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to keep sending the username and password
when following locations (using
<b>CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION</b>), even when the
hostname has changed.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:77;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:78;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:188:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_UPLOAD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to prepare for an upload.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:79;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:80;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:279:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_VERBOSE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<b>TRUE</b> to output verbose information. Writes
output to <em>STDERR</em>, or the file specified using
<b>CURLOPT_STDERR</B>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:81;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:82;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:8:"</tbody>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:83;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:84;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:8:"</table>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:85;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:86;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:84:"value should be an integer for the following values of the option parameter:
<table>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:87;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:88;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:89:"<thead>
<tr>
<th>Option</th>
<th>Set <em>value</em> to</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:89;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:90;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:304:"<tbody class="tbody">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_BUFFERSIZE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The size of the buffer to use for each read. There is no guarantee
this request will be fulfilled, however.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:91;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:92;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:378:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CLOSEPOLICY</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
One of the <b>CURLCLOSEPOLICY_*</b> values.
<blockquote class="note"><p><b>Note</b>:
</p><p>
This option is deprecated, as it was never implemented in cURL and
never had any effect.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Removed in PHP 5.6.0.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:93;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:94;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:212:"<tr>
<td><b>CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The number of seconds to wait while trying to connect. Use 0 to
wait indefinitely.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:95;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:96;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:197:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CONNECTTIMEOUT_MS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The number of milliseconds to wait while trying to connect. Use 0 to
wait indefinitely.";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:97;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:98;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:287:"If libcurl is built to use the standard system name resolver, that
portion of the connect will still use full-second resolution for
timeouts with a minimum timeout allowed of one second.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.2. Available since PHP 5.2.3.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:99;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:100;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:264:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_DNS_CACHE_TIMEOUT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The number of seconds to keep DNS entries in memory. This
option is set to 120 (2 minutes) by default.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:101;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:102;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:362:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_FTPSSLAUTH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The FTP authentication method (when is activated):
<em>CURLFTPAUTH_SSL</em> (try SSL first),
<em>CURLFTPAUTH_TLS</em> (try TLS first), or
<em>CURLFTPAUTH_DEFAULT</em> (let cURL decide).
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.12.2.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:103;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:104;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:407:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_HTTP_VERSION</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<code class="parameter">CURL_HTTP_VERSION_NONE</code> (default, lets CURL
decide which version to use),
<code class="parameter">CURL_HTTP_VERSION_1_0</code> (forces HTTP/1.0),
or <code class="parameter">CURL_HTTP_VERSION_1_1</code> (forces HTTP/1.1).
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:105;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:106;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:993:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_HTTPAUTH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p>
The HTTP authentication method(s) to use. The options are:
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_BASIC</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_DIGEST</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_GSSNEGOTIATE</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_NTLM</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_ANY</code>, and
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_ANYSAFE</code>.
</p>
<p>
The bitwise <em>|</em> (or) operator can be used to combine
more than one method. If this is done, cURL will poll the server to see
what methods it supports and pick the best one.
</p>
<p>
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_ANY</code> is an alias for
<em>CURLAUTH_BASIC | CURLAUTH_DIGEST | CURLAUTH_GSSNEGOTIATE | CURLAUTH_NTLM</em>.
</p>
<p>
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_ANYSAFE</code> is an alias for
<em>CURLAUTH_DIGEST | CURLAUTH_GSSNEGOTIATE | CURLAUTH_NTLM</em>.
</p>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:107;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:108;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:373:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_INFILESIZE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The expected size, in bytes, of the file when uploading a file to
a remote site. Note that using this option will not stop libcurl
from sending more data, as exactly what is sent depends on
<b>CURLOPT_READFUNCTION</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:109;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:110;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:347:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_LOW_SPEED_LIMIT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The transfer speed, in bytes per second, that the transfer should be
below during the count of <b>CURLOPT_LOW_SPEED_TIME</b>
seconds before PHP considers the transfer too slow and aborts.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:111;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:112;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:301:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_LOW_SPEED_TIME</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The number of seconds the transfer speed should be below
<b>CURLOPT_LOW_SPEED_LIMIT</b> before PHP considers
the transfer too slow and aborts.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:113;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:114;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:320:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_MAXCONNECTS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The maximum amount of persistent connections that are allowed.
When the limit is reached,
<b>CURLOPT_CLOSEPOLICY</b> is used to determine
which connection to close.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:115;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:116;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:261:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_MAXREDIRS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The maximum amount of HTTP redirections to follow. Use this option
alongside <b>CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:117;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:118;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:190:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PORT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
An alternative port number to connect to.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:119;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:120;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:406:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_POSTREDIR</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A bitmask of 1 (301 Moved Permanently), 2 (302 Found)
vand 4 (303 See Other) if the HTTP POST method should be maintained
when <b>CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION</b> is set and a
specific type of redirect occurs.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.19.1. Available since PHP 5.3.2.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:121;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:122;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:1202:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROTOCOLS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<p>
Bitmask of <b>CURLPROTO_*</b> values. If used, this bitmask
limits what protocols libcurl may use in the transfer. This allows you to have
a libcurl built to support a wide range of protocols but still limit specific
transfers to only be allowed to use a subset of them. By default libcurl will
accept all protocols it supports.
See also <b>CURLOPT_REDIR_PROTOCOLS</b>.
</p>
<p>
Valid protocol options are:
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_HTTP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_HTTPS</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_FTP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_FTPS</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_SCP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_SFTP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_TELNET</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_LDAP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_LDAPS</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_DICT</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_FILE</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_TFTP</code>,
<code class="parameter">CURLPROTO_ALL</code>
</p>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.19.4.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:123;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:124;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:456:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXYAUTH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The HTTP authentication method(s) to use for the proxy connection.
Use the same bitmasks as described in
<b>CURLOPT_HTTPAUTH</b>. For proxy authentication,
only <code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_BASIC</code> and
<code class="parameter">CURLAUTH_NTLM</code> are currently supported.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.7.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:125;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:126;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:255:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXYPORT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The port number of the proxy to connect to. This port number can
also be set in <b>CURLOPT_PROXY</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:127;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:128;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:325:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXYTYPE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Either <b>CURLPROXY_HTTP</b> (default),
<b>CURLPROXY_SOCKS4</b>,
<b>CURLPROXY_SOCKS5</b>,
<b>CURLPROXY_SOCKS4A</b> or
<b>CURLPROXY_SOCKS5_HOSTNAME</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:129;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:130;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:731:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_REDIR_PROTOCOLS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Bitmask of <b>CURLPROTO_*</b> values. If used, this bitmask
limits what protocols libcurl may use in a transfer that it follows to in
a redirect when <b>CURLOPT_FOLLOWLOCATION</b> is enabled.
This allows you to limit specific transfers to only be allowed to use a subset
of protocols in redirections. By default libcurl will allow all protocols
except for FILE and SCP. This is a difference compared to pre-7.19.4 versions
which unconditionally would follow to all protocols supported.
See also <b>CURLOPT_PROTOCOLS</b> for protocol constant values.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.19.4.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:131;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:132;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:204:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_RESUME_FROM</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The offset, in bytes, to resume a transfer from.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:133;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:134;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:458:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYHOST</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
1 to check the existence of a common name in the
SSL peer certificate. 2 to check the existence of
a common name and also verify that it matches the hostname
provided. In production environments the value of this option
should be kept at 2 (default value).
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Support for value 1 removed in cURL 7.28.1
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:135;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:136;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:665:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLVERSION</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
One of <b>CURL_SSLVERSION_DEFAULT</b> (0),
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_TLSv1</b> (1),
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_SSLv2</b> (2),
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_SSLv3</b> (3),
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_TLSv1_0</b> (4),
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_TLSv1_1</b> (5) or
<b>CURL_SSLVERSION_TLSv1_2</b> (6).
<blockquote class="note"><p><strong class="note">Note</strong>:
</p><p class="para">
Your best bet is to not set this and let it use the default.
Setting it to 2 or 3 is very dangerous given the known
vulnerabilities in SSLv2 and SSLv3.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:137;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:138;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:646:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_TIMECONDITION</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
How <b>CURLOPT_TIMEVALUE</b> is treated.
Use <b>CURL_TIMECOND_IFMODSINCE</b> to return the
page only if it has been modified since the time specified in
<b>CURLOPT_TIMEVALUE</b>. If it hasn\'t been modified,
a <em>"304 Not Modified"</em> header will be returned
assuming <b>CURLOPT_HEADER</code></strong> is <strong><code>TRUE</b>.
Use <code class="parameter">CURL_TIMECOND_IFUNMODSINCE</code> for the reverse
effect. <code class="parameter">CURL_TIMECOND_IFMODSINCE</code> is the
default.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:139;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:140;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:217:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_TIMEOUT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The maximum number of seconds to allow cURL functions to execute.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:141;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:142;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:173:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_TIMEOUT_MS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The maximum number of milliseconds to allow cURL functions to
execute.";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:143;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:144;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:287:"If libcurl is built to use the standard system name resolver, that
portion of the connect will still use full-second resolution for
timeouts with a minimum timeout allowed of one second.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.2. Available since PHP 5.2.3.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:145;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:146;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:330:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_TIMEVALUE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The time in seconds since January 1st, 1970. The time will be used
by <b>CURLOPT_TIMECONDITION</b>. By default,
<code class="parameter">CURL_TIMECOND_IFMODSINCE</code> is used.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:147;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:148;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:440:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_MAX_RECV_SPEED_LARGE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
If a download exceeds this speed (counted in bytes per second) on
cumulative average during the transfer, the transfer will pause to
keep the average rate less than or equal to the parameter value.
Defaults to unlimited speed.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.15.5. Available since PHP 5.4.0.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:149;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:150;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:439:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_MAX_SEND_SPEED_LARGE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
If an upload exceeds this speed (counted in bytes per second) on
cumulative average during the transfer, the transfer will pause to
keep the average rate less than or equal to the parameter value.
Defaults to unlimited speed.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.15.5. Available since PHP 5.4.0.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:151;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:152;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:392:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSH_AUTH_TYPES</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A bitmask consisting of one or more of
<b>CURLSSH_AUTH_PUBLICKEY</b>,
<b>CURLSSH_AUTH_PASSWORD</b>,
<b>CURLSSH_AUTH_HOST</b>,
<b>CURLSSH_AUTH_KEYBOARD</b>. Set to
<b>CURLSSH_AUTH_ANY</b> to let libcurl pick one.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:153;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:154;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:519:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_IPRESOLVE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Allows an application to select what kind of IP addresses to use when
resolving host names. This is only interesting when using host names that
resolve addresses using more than one version of IP, possible values are
<b>CURL_IPRESOLVE_WHATEVER</b>,
<b>CURL_IPRESOLVE_V4</b>,
<b>CURL_IPRESOLVE_V6</b>, by default
<b>CURL_IPRESOLVE_WHATEVER</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.8.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:155;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:156;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:8:"</tbody>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:157;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:158;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:8:"</table>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:159;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:160;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:113:"value should be a string for the following values of the option parameter:
<table class="doctable informaltable">";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:161;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:162;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:111:"<thead>
<tr>
<th>Option</th>
<th>Set <code class="parameter">value</code> to</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:163;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:164;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:364:"<tbody class="tbody">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CAINFO</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file holding one or more certificates to verify the
peer with. This only makes sense when used in combination with
<b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Might require an absolute path.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:165;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:166;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:256:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CAPATH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A directory that holds multiple CA certificates. Use this option
alongside <b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:167;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:168;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:350:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"Cookie: "</em> header to be
used in the HTTP request.
Note that multiple cookies are separated with a semicolon followed
by a space (e.g., "<em>fruit=apple; colour=red</em>")
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:169;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:170;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:392:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIEFILE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of the file containing the cookie data. The cookie file can
be in Netscape format, or just plain HTTP-style headers dumped into
a file.
If the name is an empty string, no cookies are loaded, but cookie
handling is still enabled.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:171;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:172;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:264:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIEJAR</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file to save all internal cookies to when the handle is closed,
e.g. after a call to curl_close.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:173;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:174;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:781:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><p class="para">
A custom request method to use instead of
<em>"GET"</em> or <em>"HEAD"</em> when doing
a HTTP request. This is useful for doing
<em>"DELETE"</em> or other, more obscure HTTP requests.
Valid values are things like <em>"GET"</em>,
<em>"POST"</em>, <em>"CONNECT"</em> and so on;
i.e. Do not enter a whole HTTP request line here. For instance,
entering <em>"GET /index.html HTTP/1.0\\r\\n\\r\\n"</em>
would be incorrect.
</p><blockquote class="note"><p><strong class="note">Note</strong>:
</p><p class="para">
Don\'t do this without making sure the server supports the custom
request method first.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:175;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:176;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:243:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_EGDSOCKET</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Like <b>CURLOPT_RANDOM_FILE</b>, except a filename
to an Entropy Gathering Daemon socket.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:177;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:178;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:453:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_ENCODING</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"Accept-Encoding: "</em> header.
This enables decoding of the response. Supported encodings are
<em>"identity"</em>, <em>"deflate"</em>, and
<em>"gzip"</em>. If an empty string, <em>""</em>,
is set, a header containing all supported encoding types is sent.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:179;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:180;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:477:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_FTPPORT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The value which will be used to get the IP address to use
for the FTP "PORT" instruction. The "PORT" instruction tells
the remote server to connect to our specified IP address.  The
string may be a plain IP address, a hostname, a network
interface name (under Unix), or just a plain \'-\' to use the
systems default IP address.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:181;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:182;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:265:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_INTERFACE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of the outgoing network interface to use. This can be an
interface name, an IP address or a host name.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:183;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:184;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:281:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_KEYPASSWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The password required to use the <b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b>
or <b>CURLOPT_SSH_PRIVATE_KEYFILE</b> private key.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:185;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:186;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:542:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_KRB4LEVEL</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The KRB4 (Kerberos 4) security level. Any of the following values
(in order from least to most powerful) are valid:
<em>"clear"</em>,
<em>"safe"</em>,
<em>"confidential"</em>,
<em>"private".</em>.
If the string does not match one of these,
<em>"private"</em> is used. Setting this option to <b>NULL</b>
will disable KRB4 security. Currently KRB4 security only works
with FTP transactions.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:187;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:188;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:1255:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<span class="simpara">
The full data to post in a HTTP "POST" operation.
To post a file, prepend a filename with <em>@</em> and
use the full path. The filetype can be explicitly specified by
following the filename with the type in the format
\'<em>;type=mimetype</em>\'. This parameter can either be
passed as a urlencoded string like \'<em>para1=val1&amp;para2=val2&amp;...</em>\'
or as an array with the field name as key and field data as value.
If <code class="parameter">value</code> is an array, the
<em>Content-Type</em> header will be set to
<em>multipart/form-data</em>.
</span>
<span class="simpara">
As of PHP 5.2.0, <code class="parameter">value</code> must be an array if
files are passed to this option with the <em>@</em> prefix.
</span>
<span class="simpara">
As of PHP 5.5.0, the <em>@</em> prefix is deprecated and
files can be sent using <a href="class.curlfile.php" class="classname">CURLFile</a>. The
<em>@</em> prefix can be disabled for safe passing of
values beginning with <em>@</em> by setting the
<b>CURLOPT_SAFE_UPLOAD</code></strong> option to <strong><code>TRUE</b>.
</span>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:189;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:190;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:192:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXY</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The HTTP proxy to tunnel requests through.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:191;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:192;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:266:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXYUSERPWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A username and password formatted as
<em>"[username]:[password]"</em> to use for the
connection to the proxy.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:193;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:194;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:222:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_RANDOM_FILE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A filename to be used to seed the random number generator for SSL.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:195;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:196;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:337:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_RANGE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Range(s) of data to retrieve in the format
<em>"X-Y"</em> where X or Y are optional. HTTP transfers
also support several intervals, separated with commas in the format
<em>"X-Y,N-M"</em>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:197;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:198;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:229:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_REFERER</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"Referer: "</em> header to be used
in a HTTP request.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:199;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:200;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:428:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSH_HOST_PUBLIC_KEY_MD5</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A string containing 32 hexadecimal digits. The string should be the
MD5 checksum of the remote host\'s public key, and libcurl will reject
the connection to the host unless the md5sums match.
This option is only for SCP and SFTP transfers.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.17.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:201;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:202;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:382:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSH_PUBLIC_KEYFILE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The file name for your public key. If not used, libcurl defaults to
$HOME/.ssh/id_dsa.pub if the HOME environment variable is set,
and just "id_dsa.pub" in the current directory if HOME is not set.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:203;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:204;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:459:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSH_PRIVATE_KEYFILE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The file name for your private key. If not used, libcurl defaults to
$HOME/.ssh/id_dsa if the HOME environment variable is set,
and just "id_dsa" in the current directory if HOME is not set.
If the file is password-protected, set the password with
<b>CURLOPT_KEYPASSWD</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:205;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:206;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:266:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSL_CIPHER_LIST</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A list of ciphers to use for SSL. For example,
<em>RC4-SHA</em> and <em>TLSv1</em> are valid
cipher lists.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:207;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:208;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:210:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLCERT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file containing a PEM formatted certificate.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:209;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:210;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:226:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLCERTPASSWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The password required to use the
<b>CURLOPT_SSLCERT</b> certificate.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:211;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:212;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:291:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLCERTTYPE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The format of the certificate. Supported formats are
<em>"PEM"</em> (default), <em>"DER"</em>,
and <em>"ENG"</em>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.9.3.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:213;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:214;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:249:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLENGINE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The identifier for the crypto engine of the private SSL key
specified in <b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:215;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:216;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:237:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLENGINE_DEFAULT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The identifier for the crypto engine used for asymmetric crypto
operations.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:217;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:218;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:199:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file containing a private SSL key.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:219;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:220;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:480:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLKEYPASSWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><p class="para">
The secret password needed to use the private SSL key specified in
<b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b>.
</p><blockquote class="note"><p><strong class="note">Note</strong>:
</p><p class="para">
Since this option contains a sensitive password, remember to keep
the PHP script it is contained within safe.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:221;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:222;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:312:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_SSLKEYTYPE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The key type of the private SSL key specified in
<b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b>. Supported key types are
<em>"PEM"</em> (default), <em>"DER"</em>,
and <em>"ENG"</em>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:223;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:224;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:246:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_URL</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The URL to fetch. This can also be set when initializing a
session with {@see curl_init()}</span>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:225;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:226;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:234:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_USERAGENT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"User-Agent: "</em> header to be
used in a HTTP request.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:227;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:228;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:248:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_USERPWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A username and password formatted as
<em>"[username]:[password]"</em> to use for the
connection.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:229;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:230;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:8:"</tbody>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:231;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:232;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:47:"</table>
<table class="doctable informaltable">";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:233;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:234;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:111:"<thead>
<tr>
<th>Option</th>
<th>Set <code class="parameter">value</code> to</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:235;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:236;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:364:"<tbody class="tbody">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CAINFO</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file holding one or more certificates to verify the
peer with. This only makes sense when used in combination with
<b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Might require an absolute path.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:237;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:238;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:256:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CAPATH</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
A directory that holds multiple CA certificates. Use this option
alongside <b>CURLOPT_SSL_VERIFYPEER</b>.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:239;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:240;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:350:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"Cookie: "</em> header to be
used in the HTTP request.
Note that multiple cookies are separated with a semicolon followed
by a space (e.g., "<em>fruit=apple; colour=red</em>")
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:241;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:242;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:392:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIEFILE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of the file containing the cookie data. The cookie file can
be in Netscape format, or just plain HTTP-style headers dumped into
a file.
If the name is an empty string, no cookies are loaded, but cookie
handling is still enabled.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:243;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:244;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:264:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_COOKIEJAR</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of a file to save all internal cookies to when the handle is closed,
e.g. after a call to curl_close.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:245;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:246;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:781:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_CUSTOMREQUEST</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><p class="para">
A custom request method to use instead of
<em>"GET"</em> or <em>"HEAD"</em> when doing
a HTTP request. This is useful for doing
<em>"DELETE"</em> or other, more obscure HTTP requests.
Valid values are things like <em>"GET"</em>,
<em>"POST"</em>, <em>"CONNECT"</em> and so on;
i.e. Do not enter a whole HTTP request line here. For instance,
entering <em>"GET /index.html HTTP/1.0\\r\\n\\r\\n"</em>
would be incorrect.
</p><blockquote class="note"><p><strong class="note">Note</strong>:
</p><p class="para">
Don\'t do this without making sure the server supports the custom
request method first.
</p>
</blockquote>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:247;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:248;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:243:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_EGDSOCKET</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Like <b>CURLOPT_RANDOM_FILE</b>, except a filename
to an Entropy Gathering Daemon socket.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:249;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:250;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:453:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_ENCODING</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The contents of the <em>"Accept-Encoding: "</em> header.
This enables decoding of the response. Supported encodings are
<em>"identity"</em>, <em>"deflate"</em>, and
<em>"gzip"</em>. If an empty string, <em>""</em>,
is set, a header containing all supported encoding types is sent.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.10.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:251;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:252;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:477:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_FTPPORT</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The value which will be used to get the IP address to use
for the FTP "PORT" instruction. The "PORT" instruction tells
the remote server to connect to our specified IP address.  The
string may be a plain IP address, a hostname, a network
interface name (under Unix), or just a plain \'-\' to use the
systems default IP address.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:253;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:254;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:265:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_INTERFACE</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The name of the outgoing network interface to use. This can be an
interface name, an IP address or a host name.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:255;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:256;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:281:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_KEYPASSWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The password required to use the <b>CURLOPT_SSLKEY</b>
or <b>CURLOPT_SSH_PRIVATE_KEYFILE</b> private key.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
Added in cURL 7.16.1.
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:257;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:258;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:542:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_KRB4LEVEL</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The KRB4 (Kerberos 4) security level. Any of the following values
(in order from least to most powerful) are valid:
<em>"clear"</em>,
<em>"safe"</em>,
<em>"confidential"</em>,
<em>"private".</em>.
If the string does not match one of these,
<em>"private"</em> is used. Setting this option to <b>NULL</b>
will disable KRB4 security. Currently KRB4 security only works
with FTP transactions.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:259;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:260;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:1255:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_POSTFIELDS</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
<span class="simpara">
The full data to post in a HTTP "POST" operation.
To post a file, prepend a filename with <em>@</em> and
use the full path. The filetype can be explicitly specified by
following the filename with the type in the format
\'<em>;type=mimetype</em>\'. This parameter can either be
passed as a urlencoded string like \'<em>para1=val1&amp;para2=val2&amp;...</em>\'
or as an array with the field name as key and field data as value.
If <code class="parameter">value</code> is an array, the
<em>Content-Type</em> header will be set to
<em>multipart/form-data</em>.
</span>
<span class="simpara">
As of PHP 5.2.0, <code class="parameter">value</code> must be an array if
files are passed to this option with the <em>@</em> prefix.
</span>
<span class="simpara">
As of PHP 5.5.0, the <em>@</em> prefix is deprecated and
files can be sent using <a href="class.curlfile.php" class="classname">CURLFile</a>. The
<em>@</em> prefix can be disabled for safe passing of
values beginning with <em>@</em> by setting the
<b>CURLOPT_SAFE_UPLOAD</code></strong> option to <strong><code>TRUE</b>.
</span>
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:261;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:262;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:192:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXY</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
The HTTP proxy to tunnel requests through.
</td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
</td>
</tr>";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:263;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:0:"";s:58:"' . "\0" . 'PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode' . "\0" . 'attributes";a:0:{}}i:264;O:46:"PHPStan\\PhpDocParser\\Ast\\PhpDoc\\PhpDocTextNode":2:{s:4:"text";s:266:"<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: top;"><b>CURLOPT_PROXYUSERPWD</b></td>
<td style="vertical-align: top;">
